        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/12–2047</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé of the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tsarapkin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State for Economic
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thorp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 250</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-20">December 20,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acknowledging receipt of your letter of December 11, 1947, concerning eight
                    lend-lease vessels, I hereby inform you that the Government of the Union of
                    Soviet Socialist Republics considers that this question is subject to decision
                    in the course of the general lend-lease settlement, concerning which concrete
                    proposals were presented by the Soviet side to the American side on December 16,
                    1947.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsarapkin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
